STEARN, Appellant, v. HESDORFER, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 5, 1894.) Action by Bertha Stearn against Louis Hesdorfer.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and BISOHOPP and PRYOR, JJ.

Hayman & Rosenthal, for appellant M. A. Kurscheedt, for respondent

No opinion. Motion to affirm judgment for nonservice of'printed papers on appeal denied, without costs.
